    <h3>Patient Details</h3>
    <p><strong>Name:</strong> Holly Burton</p>
    <p><strong>DOB:</strong> 19/02/2003 (Age 21)</p>
    <p><strong>Pronouns:</strong> [e.g., She/Her, He/Him, They/Them - *Not
      stated in video, example for generalization*]</p>
    <p><strong>Gender Identity:</strong> [e.g., Woman, Man, Non-binary - *Not
      stated in video, example for generalization*]</p>
    <h3>Presenting Complaint (PC)</h3>
    <p>Concerns about a possible Sexually Transmitted Infection (STI).</p>
    <h3>History of Presenting Complaint (HPC)</h3>
    <p>For the past 7 days, patient has experienced:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Unusual genital discharge: described as yellowish, more watery than
        usual, and malodorous (from vagina).</li>
      <li>Burning sensation on urination (dysuria).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Denies: increased urinary frequency, pelvic/abdominal pain, fever, anal
      symptoms (discharge/pain), external genital itching/soreness/lumps,
      intermenstrual bleeding, post-coital bleeding, or dyspareunia.</p>
    <h3>Ideas, Concerns, and Expectations (ICE)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Ideas:</strong> Believes symptoms may be due to an STI
        (possibly Chlamydia) from a recent sexual partner.</li>
      <li><strong>Concerns:</strong> Worried it might be "something a bit more
        serious" as symptoms are new to them.</li>
      <li><strong>Expectations:</strong> Hopes for a full STI screen and
        appropriate treatment if an infection is found.</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="Sexual_history_section">
      <h3>Sexual Activity &amp; Partners</h3>
      <p><br>
        <br>
        &bull;--- Do you use condoms?&nbsp; or Do you practice safe sex all the
        time?(indirect)<br>
        &bull;--- When was the last time you had unprotected sex?<br>
        &bull;--- Is your sexual partner male or female? What is your sexual
        orientation</p>
      <p><strong>General Approach to Sex:</strong>- Are you sexually active? </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Monogamous, - Are you in a stable relationship?</li>
        <li>non-monogamous, - Do you have any other partners? </li>
        <li>number of current partners</li>
        <li>Which route of sex do you prefer? Oral, Vaginal or Anal?</li>
      </ol>
      <p><strong>Recent Sexual Contacts (within last 3-6 months, or as
          relevant): --</strong> - How many partners do you have?</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Most Recent Partner (approx. 15 days ago):</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>Partner's gender(s)/identity: Male</li>
            <li>Relationship type: Casual ("one-off at a party")</li>
            <li>Types of sexual contact: Vaginal, Oral (patient performed and
              received), anal</li>
            <li>Barrier use (condoms, dental dams etc.): No</li>
            <li>Partner's origin (if known/relevant): UK</li>
            <li>Known STI status of partner: Unknown</li>
            <li>Encounter was consensual: Yes</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Partner prior (approx. 2 months ago):</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>.............................</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Partner prior (approx. 3 months ago):</strong>
          <ul>
            <li>.............................</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Total number of partners:</strong> Approx. 3 in the last 3
        months, 5 in the last 12 months.</p>
      <p><strong>Gender(s) of partners in last 12 months:</strong> are All male
        your partners male?. </p>
      <p><strong>Use of sex toys:</strong> [D you use any sex toys?</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Shared/not shared, </li>
        <li>cleaning practices - </li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Female specific </h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Genital skin changes:</strong> e.g., <em>lichen </em>sclerosus,
          <em>atrophy</em>, or lesions.</li>
        <li><strong>Vulval itching or soreness:</strong> consider candidiasis, <em>lichen
            </em>sclerosus, or STIs.</li>
        <li><strong>Dysuria:</strong> assess for UTIs or urethritis.</li>
        <li><strong>Abnormal vaginal discharge:</strong> inquire about changes
          in colour, consistency, volume, or odour.</li>
        <li><strong>Abnormal vaginal <em>bleeding</em>:</strong> including
          post-coital, intermenstrual, or postmenopausal bleeding.</li>
        <li><strong>Dyspareunia:</strong> differentiate between superficial
          (e.g., atrophy) and deep (e.g., endometriosis) pain.</li>
        <li><strong>Abdominal or pelvic pain:</strong> use SOCRATES to
          characterize the pain.</li>
        <li><strong>Changes in menstrual cycle:</strong> note irregularities,
          amenorrhoea, or menorrhagia.</li>
        <li><strong>Systemic symptoms:</strong> such as fever, fatigue, or
          weight loss.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>male specific</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Testicular pain or swelling:</strong> evaluate for <b>epididymitis</b>,
          <b>torsion</b>, or <b>orchitis</b>.</li>
        <li><strong>Itching or sore skin:</strong> consider dermatitis,
          candidiasis, or STIs.</li>
        <li><strong>Skin lesions:</strong> assess for ulcers, vesicles, or
          warts.</li>
        <li><strong>Urethral discharge:</strong> note colour, consistency, and
          associated symptoms.</li>
        <li><strong>Dysuria:</strong> inquire about burning or pain during
          urination.</li>
        <li><strong>Systemic symptoms:</strong> such as fever, malaise, or joint
          pain.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Past STI History &amp; Screening</h3>
      <p>No previously diagnosed STIs.</p>
      <p>Last STI screen: Approx. 4 months ago (at university), included blood
        test (finger prick) and swab. Results: All clear.</p>
      <h3>Blood-Borne Virus (BBV) / Other Infection Risk Assessment</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Ever had sexual contact with partner(s) from a country with high
          prevalence of HIV/Hepatitis B/C? Yes, one partner from Spain (Madrid)
          approx. 2 years ago.</li>
        <li>Ever had sexual contact with a partner who has sex with men? (If
          applicable based on patient/partner gender): No.</li>
        <li>Ever had sexual contact with a partner known to inject drugs? No.</li>
        <li>Ever had sexual contact with a partner known to have HIV, Syphilis,
          or Hepatitis? No.</li>
        <li>History of tattoos or piercings (and safety precautions taken)? No
          tattoos. (Piercings not detailed).</li>
        <li>Ever injected drugs? No.</li>
        <li>Ever shared drug snorting equipment (e.g., notes, straws)? No
          (reports using own key).</li>
        <li>Ever paid for sex or been paid for sex? No.</li>
        <li>Hepatitis B Vaccination status: Unsure.</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Reproductive Health / Menstrual History (if applicable)</h3>
      <p>Menstruates regularly. Last Menstrual Period (LMP) was 3 weeks ago.</p>
      <h3>Contraception</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Currently using: Combined oral contraceptive pill (Rigevidon).</li>
        <li>Compliance: Good, uses phone alarm, no missed pills reported.</li>
        <li>Concerns about current method / Interest in other methods: [Not
          explored in video]</li>
      </ol>
      <h3>Past Obstetric / Gynaecological / Urological / Genital Health History
        (as applicable)</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>pregnancies</li>
        <ol>
          <li>current</li>
          <ol>
            <li class="derma">Seborrhoeic keratosis increses with pregancy , sun
              exposure</li>
          </ol>
          <li>previous </li>
        </ol>
        <li>HPV vaccination: Yes, received at school.</li>
        <li>Cervical screening history: Not yet eligible based on age.</li>
        <li>Other relevant past conditions/surgeries: None reported.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <h3>Social History (Relevant to Sexual Health)</h3>
    <p><strong>Living Situation:</strong> University student (History major),
      lives with friends in shared accommodation.</p>
    <p><strong>Smoking:</strong> Occasional social smoker (e.g., "odd tab" when
      out).</p>
    <p><strong>Alcohol:</strong> Drinks approx. 3 times a week, typically 5
      double vodka and cokes per occasion (estimated ~30 units/week).</p>
    <p><strong>Recreational Drug Use:</strong> </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Cocaine: Used "occasionally" (last use ~4 months ago, estimates 1-2
        times/year).</li>
      <li>Route of administration: Snorting (reports using own house key, not
        sharing equipment).</li>
      <li>Other drugs: Denies other drug use.</li>
    </ul>
